left class=m><span class=title> Re: paladin Defensive</span><hr size=1> The entire purpose of Defensive and related disciplines is the &quot;reduces damage by x%&quot;.  To argue that self-healing is similar to Defensive is flawed.  Clerics get Complete Healing, but one would hardly say that they get the Defensive discipline.  <br><br>Don't get me wrong, I think Paladins make great main tanks in most situations.  I don't consider myself uber (by any means), but my typical, single group has taken out some difficult stuff with only myself as the tank.<br><br>Paladins can almost match warriors' HP and AC both unbuffed and raid-buffed.  The problem comes in when the hits start getting upwards of 400 HP a pop; in these situations Paladin-tanking starts to buckle.  On mobs that hit for 600+ (especially quadding), Paladin-tanking is out of the question.  Even Sup. Healing, HWoP, or CC will only be, at best, mitigation for a single round of melee damage from this level of NPC.<br><br>Not arguing that Paladins should get a defensive discipline, nor that Paladins are poor tanks, nor that Paladins are useless.  I love this class.  I'm just saying that the Defensive /disc's main feature is to reduce all those nasty 700 hits down to 400's; something we just can't come close to doing. <p><font color="0000aa"><h5>Vladimirr D'Benefiece<br>Officer, Order of the White Dragon<br>Deepwater Knight<br>In Service of our Good and Gracious Oceanlord, Prexus<br>Bristlebane Server<br><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=17434">Click here for equipment listing</a><br></h5></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvladimirrdbenefiece.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vladimirr DBenefiece</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.execpc.com/~jwnrski/shield.gif" BORDER=0> at: 3/14/02 7:20:28 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubeldukil.sho