 end melee.<br><br>All of its effect on one person - this is a plus, not a minus.  THE number one problem with most high end mobs is their melee damage to the single person they are hitting.  If that one single person has defensive up, the mobs damage output is slashed.<br><br>High-ish end mobs and up are doing hundreds of damage per second - defensive is liable to mitigate tens-hundreds of thousand damage in three minutes on a hard hitting mob.<br><br>Finally, by reducing the overall damage taken, defensive reduces the amount of healing needed.  This both reduces the chance of healers getting aggro, and increases the chance that the tank will actually live long enough to get healed.<br><br><br>Paladins can mitigate attritional damage very nicely.  But in my opinion that is in no way comparable to defensive disc.<br><br>PS - Pally's don't need defensive, IMO.  It's overpowered and I think it's staying right where it is. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwulf9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wulf9</A> at: 3/14/02 7:58:43 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvladimirrdbenefiece.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vladimirr DBenefiece</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.execpc.com/~jwnrski/shield.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 505<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 7:58:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14849.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.execpc.com/~jwnrski/vladsig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: paladin Defensiv