ds have time to adjust and cast healing spells.<br><br>When an MA dies on a Defensive requiring mob, several SA's can be crushed simply because ecen with defensive up, if the heal order is not quick to swich all the heals land too late to save the new tank.<br><br>When I was lower level (and I hate to say this but it is SO true) I didn't fully ubderstand the severity myself. Now that I am 59 and have experienced some of the mobs myself, I see just how powerful defensive is and how much superior it makes full warriors against super mobs.<br><br>Instant on, no cast time, long duration, non interuptable, defensive is just compltely superior to any option that a Paladins can muster.<br><br>/sigh <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105286">Gilfalas Elaandrin</a>, Lvl 59 Knight of Tunare & Defender of Nature<br>Bertoxxulous Server<br><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath">Paladins Of Norrath</a> Messageboard Admin<br>Member of <a href="http://www.fedupnow.com/">Dragon Council</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvladimirrdbenefiece.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vladimirr DBenefiece</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.execpc.com/~jwnrski/shield.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 506<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/14/02 9:39:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14849.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.execpc.com/~jwnrski/vladsig.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: paladin Defensive</span><hr size=1> It all comes down to percentages versus fixed values.<br><br>The way you're looking at it is not wrong, actually it's correct when applied to non-high end mobs.  I will attempt to explain.<br><br>Defensive reduces damage by 45%, per round.<br>Paladin healing can reduce damage by, let's say, 100 per round.<br><br>--------------------<br><br>The following situation is theoretical:<br><br>If there was a level 30 Warrior with Defensive, and a level 30 Paladin with CC/SH/HWoP/Lay Hands, the Paladin would be the better tank.  Stuff then is typically hitting you for 50.  50% of that would mean the warrior was being hit for 25 a round.<br><br>The paladin, however, with his 100 HP per round, would never lose any health.  (-50 + 100 = 50 HP gained a round)<br><br>If the fight took 1000 rounds, the Paladin would actually gain 50000 HP, where the warrior would lose 25000 HP.<br><br>--------------------<br><br>Now fast forward to level 60.<br><br>Stuff then can hit you for 700 damage.  50% of that would mean the warrior was being hit for 350 a round.<br><br>The paladin, however, with his 100 HP per round, be hit for 600 a round.  (-700 + 100 = 600 HP lost a round)<br><br>If the fight took 1000 rounds, the Warrior would lose 350,000 HP, where the Paladin would lose 600,000 (if he managed to somehow get off every heal, and not run out of mana either).<br><br>-------------------<br><br>This is much like Complete Healing (100%)  being vastly better than Superior Healing (~500hp).  At level 1, when you have 20 HP, a 500 point heal seems like a lot; and Complete Healing would only heal you for 20.  But once you have 5000 HP, a 500 point heal is a drop in the bucket, and Complete Heal is the only thing that's going to save your arse. <p><font color="0000aa"><h5>Vladimirr D'Benefiece<br>Officer, Order of the White Dragon<br>Deepwater Knight<br>In Service of our Good and Gracious Oceanlord, Prexus<br>Bristlebane Server<br><a href = "